comment.body:
Any news on this one? 

@Benjozork already showed a prototype 1,5 year ago. So I was wondering, if there is some kind of alpha/beta release available that we may be able to contribute to instead of doing work in parallel or even duplicate?

We are currently evaluating options to move from our legacy system (X-Plane 10 based model + [Extplane](https://github.com/vranki/ExtPlane)  + custom display implementation) to a modern setup with MSFS and this A320 model.
We are just wondering if it is worth to wait for this feature or start our own implementation, which may result in an adaption of the current Extplane and display software.
I hope this is correct, clippy complained and it made sense to me.

pull_request.title: feat(bleed): Ground air start
pull_request.body:
<!-- ⚠⚠ Do not delete this pull request template! ⚠⚠ -->
<!-- Pull requests that do not follow this template are likely to be ignored. -->

<!-- Add the issues this PR fixes here. If no issues are related to this PR, then this line can be removed. -->
<!-- Add further issues with a full "Fixes #[issue_no]" line to ensure GitHub closes each one when the PR is merged. -->
Fixes #[issue_no]

## Summary of Changes
<!-- Please provide a summary of changes for this pull request, ensuring all changes are explained. -->

This PR is implementing a basic Air Starter Unit to be able to start engines or supply the PACKs without the APU.

The most complicated part of this is the handling of the MSFS APU since that is still required for the engines to start.
In this case I decided to have the FADEC control when the MSFS APU is consuming fuel to deal with the fact that we need it to provide bleed pressure for the MSFS engine model.

Additionally while working on this PR, I had issues with the way we start the engines in the sim. Because of the lack of a real bleed system in MSFS engines start when they have fuel and there is a bleed source somewhere in the aircraft.

This leads to engines being able to start when no actual bleed air is reaching them.

I therefore masked the TOGGLE_STARTER#ID# event in the FADEC code and use the SET_STARTER_HELD event to actually command an engine start when all requirements are fulfilled. Since we have a custom bleed system I also made sure the engines are only able to start when they have enough bleed pressure. Should that pressure disappear before 25% N2 is reached, the engines will stop. 

That part of the work can be seen as a jump off point for a proper EIU.



## Screenshots (if necessary)
<!-- If your PR includes visual changes, screenshots from before and after your change should always be included. -->
<!-- Please make your best efforts to provide useful before and after screenshots. They should match camera angle, zoom, size, time of day, etc. -->

![image](https://github.com/flybywiresim/aircraft/assets/5833783/1fc096d3-a6f2-48b5-a412-af0631acd1d2)
![Ground EFB page with ASU](https://github.com/flybywiresim/aircraft/assets/5833783/9fd7c6fe-e154-4b7b-99b2-158a0456cea6)



## References
<!-- You should be making changes based on some kind of a reference (manuals, videos, IRL photos). P3D/xplane/fsx references will only be accepted if we believe that one cannot reasonably obtain a better source. Please post screenshots of the references you used. Ask around in the discord for how to find references for what you are working on. Exceptions will probably be made for IRL A320 pilots and engineers. -->

<!-- If you are making a pull request related to the MCDU, please make sure you are ONLY referencing the Honeywell Pegasus Step 1A (Rev 0), 2009 edition manual. -->
<!-- If you do not have this manual, please ask on our discord for assistance -->

## Additional context
<!-- Add any other context about the pull request here. -->

<!-- You may optionally provide your discord username, so that we may contact you directly about the issue. -->
Discord username (if different from GitHub): \_Chaoz_

## Testing instructions
<!-- Detail how this PR should be tested by QA. Try to list important items that need checking, either directly changed by this PR or that could be affected by it -->

1. Start C&D
2. Apply ground power to the aircraft
3. Align ADIRS
4. Switch the EFB on and open the Ground Services Page
5. Activate the Air starter unit and observe the BLEED SD page
6. Pressure should build on the Indication above the left engine 
7. Pack 1 should turn on as well
8. open the cross bleed valve by manually turning the X BLEED selector to OPEN
9. observe a pressure rise in the right system indication
10. Pack 2 should turn on
11. Turn on the left and right engine fuel pumps
12. Turn the ENG MODE SELECTOR to IGN/START 
13. Turn the ENG 2 MASTER to ON 
14. Eng 2 should startup normally
15. Turn ENG MODE SELECTOR to NORM
16. Turn off Eng 2
17. Turn X BLEED selector to SHUT
18. Repeat steps 12 and 13
21. Eng 2 should only start for a bit before stopping
22. Turn X BLEED selector to OPEN
23. Wait for pressure to build up again
24. Cycling ENG MASTER should make ENG 2 start
25. Turn X BLEED selector to SHUT while N2 is below 25%
26. ENG 2 should stop after system pressure falls to around 14 PSI
27. Turn X BLEED selector to OPEN
28. Wait for pressure to build up again
29. Cycling ENG MASTER should make ENG 2 start
30. Turn X BLEED selector to SHUT while N2 is at 25% or greater
31. ENG 2 should continue starting normally

Every new commit to this PR will cause a new A32NX artifact to be created, built, and uploaded.

1. Click on the **Checks** tab on the PR
1. On the left side, click on the bottom **PR** tab
1. Click on the **A32NX** download link at the bottom of the page

pull_request.title: feat(bleed): Ground air start
pull_request.body:
<!-- ⚠⚠ Do not delete this pull request template! ⚠⚠ -->
<!-- Pull requests that do not follow this template are likely to be ignored. -->

<!-- Add the issues this PR fixes here. If no issues are related to this PR, then this line can be removed. -->
<!-- Add further issues with a full "Fixes #[issue_no]" line to ensure GitHub closes each one when the PR is merged. -->
Fixes #[issue_no]

## Summary of Changes
<!-- Please provide a summary of changes for this pull request, ensuring all changes are explained. -->

This PR is implementing a basic Air Starter Unit to be able to start engines or supply the PACKs without the APU.

The most complicated part of this is the handling of the MSFS APU since that is still required for the engines to start.
In this case I decided to have the FADEC control when the MSFS APU is consuming fuel to deal with the fact that we need it to provide bleed pressure for the MSFS engine model.

Additionally while working on this PR, I had issues with the way we start the engines in the sim. Because of the lack of a real bleed system in MSFS engines start when they have fuel and there is a bleed source somewhere in the aircraft.

This leads to engines being able to start when no actual bleed air is reaching them.

I therefore masked the TOGGLE_STARTER#ID# event in the FADEC code and use the SET_STARTER_HELD event to actually command an engine start when all requirements are fulfilled. Since we have a custom bleed system I also made sure the engines are only able to start when they have enough bleed pressure. Should that pressure disappear before 25% N2 is reached, the engines will stop. 

That part of the work can be seen as a jump off point for a proper EIU.



## Screenshots (if necessary)
<!-- If your PR includes visual changes, screenshots from before and after your change should always be included. -->
<!-- Please make your best efforts to provide useful before and after screenshots. They should match camera angle, zoom, size, time of day, etc. -->

![image](https://github.com/flybywiresim/aircraft/assets/5833783/1fc096d3-a6f2-48b5-a412-af0631acd1d2)
![Ground EFB page with ASU](https://github.com/flybywiresim/aircraft/assets/5833783/9fd7c6fe-e154-4b7b-99b2-158a0456cea6)



## References
<!-- You should be making changes based on some kind of a reference (manuals, videos, IRL photos). P3D/xplane/fsx references will only be accepted if we believe that one cannot reasonably obtain a better source. Please post screenshots of the references you used. Ask around in the discord for how to find references for what you are working on. Exceptions will probably be made for IRL A320 pilots and engineers. -->

<!-- If you are making a pull request related to the MCDU, please make sure you are ONLY referencing the Honeywell Pegasus Step 1A (Rev 0), 2009 edition manual. -->
<!-- If you do not have this manual, please ask on our discord for assistance -->

## Additional context
<!-- Add any other context about the pull request here. -->

<!-- You may optionally provide your discord username, so that we may contact you directly about the issue. -->
Discord username (if different from GitHub): \_Chaoz_

## Testing instructions
<!-- Detail how this PR should be tested by QA. Try to list important items that need checking, either directly changed by this PR or that could be affected by it -->

1. Start C&D
2. Apply ground power to the aircraft
3. Align ADIRS
4. Switch the EFB on and open the Ground Services Page
5. Activate the Air starter unit and observe the BLEED SD page
6. Pressure should build on the Indication above the left engine 
7. Pack 1 should turn on as well
8. open the cross bleed valve by manually turning the X BLEED selector to OPEN
9. observe a pressure rise in the right system indication
10. Pack 2 should turn on
11. Turn on the left and right engine fuel pumps
12. Turn the ENG MODE SELECTOR to IGN/START 
13. Turn the ENG 2 MASTER to ON 
14. Eng 2 should startup normally
15. Turn ENG MODE SELECTOR to NORM
16. Turn off Eng 2
17. Turn X BLEED selector to SHUT
18. Repeat steps 12 and 13
21. Eng 2 should only start for a bit before stopping
22. Turn X BLEED selector to OPEN
23. Wait for pressure to build up again
24. Cycling ENG MASTER should make ENG 2 start
25. Turn X BLEED selector to SHUT while N2 is below 25%
26. ENG 2 should stop after system pressure falls to around 14 PSI
27. Turn X BLEED selector to OPEN
28. Wait for pressure to build up again
29. Cycling ENG MASTER should make ENG 2 start
30. Turn X BLEED selector to SHUT while N2 is at 25% or greater
31. ENG 2 should continue starting normally


<!-- DO NOT DELETE THIS -->
## How to download the PR for QA

Every new commit to this PR will cause a new A32NX artifact to be created, built, and uploaded.

1. Make sure you are signed in to GitHub
1. Click on the **Checks** tab on the PR
1. On the left side, click on the bottom **PR** tab
1. Click on the **A32NX** download link at the bottom of the page

pull_request.body:
<!-- ⚠⚠ Do not delete this pull request template! ⚠⚠ -->
<!-- Pull requests that do not follow this template are likely to be ignored. -->

<!-- Add the issues this PR fixes here. If no issues are related to this PR, then this line can be removed. -->
<!-- Add further issues with a full "Fixes #[issue_no]" line to ensure GitHub closes each one when the PR is merged. -->
Fixes #[issue_no]

## Summary of Changes
<!-- Please provide a summary of changes for this pull request, ensuring all changes are explained. -->

On startup in C/D the aircraft plays a master warning until the startup EWD messages are empty. This was caused by the pseudo FWC checking whether the aircraft was on ground only after checking for dual engine failure which meant that the FWC didn't update the on ground status until after the check for dual engine failure and since the on ground status was initialized with false, the dual eng failure triggered on initial load.

This PR changes the order of those checks so that the setting of the on ground status happens first.

commits.message:
fix(mcdu): improve PERF pages (#8205)

* Implement CHECK SPEED MODE message

* Improve layout on PERF pages

* Allow modification of PRED TO altitudes

* Fix displayed managed speed

* Take speed constraint into account for clb speed

* Update changelog

* Fix slash formatting

* Use Mach 0.80 for DES CAS selection only

* Fix input parsing

* Fix layout before FROM/TO entry

* Inhibit CHECK SPEED MODE in excessive attitude

* Fix slash formatting again

* Allow Mach only entries

* Make * on CRZ page small

* fix: changelog 0.12

---------

Co-authored-by: Michael Corcoran <tracer@outlook.co.nz>

Fixes #[issue_no]

## Summary of Changes
<!-- Please provide a summary of changes for this pull request, ensuring all changes are explained. -->
Capt ND will show ILS2,  FO ND will show ILS1. This was a regression that is fixed now

## Screenshots (if necessary)

P3D/xplane/fsx references will only be accepted if we believe that one cannot reasonably obtain a better source. Please post screenshots of the references you used. Ask around in the discord for how to find references for what you are working on. Exceptions will probably be made for IRL A320 pilots and engineers. -->

<!-- If you are making a pull request related to the MCDU, please make sure you are ONLY referencing the Honeywell Pegasus Step 1A (Rev 0), 2009 edition manual. -->
<!-- If you do not have this manual, please ask on our discord for assistance -->

## Additional context
<!-- Add any other context about the pull request here. -->

<!-- You may optionally provide your discord username, so that we may contact you directly about the issue. -->
Discord username (if different from GitHub):

## Testing instructions
<!-- Detail how this PR should be tested by QA. Try to list important items that need checking, either directly changed by this PR or that could be affected by it -->

<!-- DO NOT DELETE THIS -->
## How to download the PR for QA

Every new commit to this PR will cause a new A32NX artifact to be created, built, and uploaded.

1. Make sure you are signed in to GitHub
1. Click on the **Checks** tab on the PR
1. On the left side, click on the bottom **PR** tab
1. Click on the **A32NX** download link at the bottom of the page
